The paper introduces a neural network architecture for learning generalised policies for probabilistic planning problems, which involves artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The proposed network is designed to mimic the relational structure of planning problems, which relates to robotics (cs.RO) and programming languages (cs.PL). The paper also discusses a training method that balances exploration and supervised training, which is relevant to control systems (cs.SY).
